ity and {DIC} concentration, and decrease of {pH} at surface. The new, high-resolution reanalysis, open and freely available from the Copernicus Marine Service, allows users from different communities to investigate the spatial and temporal variability of 12 biogeochemical variables and fluxes at different scales (from mesoscale to basin-wide and from daily to multi-year) and the interaction between physical and biogeochemical processes shaping the Mediterranean marine ecosystem functioning.},
